HEADWORD: Cinclidae
<hw>Cinclidae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a natural family of birds
comprising the water ouzels, also called dippers, which dive under water
in flowing streams.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Cinclidae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
